# Phase 8.x Enhancement – Release Branch Resolution, Branch Cut Status & UI Simplification

## Objective

Enhance the `release_branches` data model and Fetch Components workflow to improve release branch tracking, branch cut validation, production branch resolution, and library handling. These enhancements are incremental to the previous implementation and must not break any existing functionality.

---

# Acceptance Criteria

## AC-1: Add Branch Cut Status Column

Enhance the `release_branches` table by introducing a new status column.

Suggested names (choose the most appropriate one):

- `branch_cut_status`
- `release_branch_status`
- `branch_resolution_status`

Preferred value examples:

- `BRANCH_CUT_COMPLETED`
- `BRANCH_CUT_PENDING`

Avoid storing free-text messages.

---

## AC-2: Automatically Calculate Branch Cut Status

After the Current Branch has been resolved, determine whether the release branch has already been cut.

Use the existing Fix Version metadata.

Each Fix Version already contains:

- From Date
- To Date

Example:

```
Fix Version
2026.07.18

From
12-Jul-2026

To
18-Jul-2026
```

The existing Current Branch selection logic already determines the latest release branch for the selected Fix Version.

Reuse that logic.

---

## AC-3: Branch Cut Completed Rule

If the resolved Current Branch belongs to the selected Fix Version window:

```
Branch Cut Status

=

BRANCH_CUT_COMPLETED
```

Example

Selected Fix Version

```
12-Jul → 18-Jul
```

Resolved Current Branch

```
release/2026.07.18
```

Status

```
BRANCH_CUT_COMPLETED
```

---

## AC-4: Branch Cut Pending Rule

If no Current Branch exists for the selected Fix Version window:

```
Branch Cut Status

=

BRANCH_CUT_PENDING
```

This indicates that the release branch has not yet been created.

---

## AC-5: Store Branch Cut Status in Database

Persist the calculated status into the `release_branches` table.

It must be recalculated every time:

- Fetch Components
- Force Refresh
- Generate Report
- Component Refresh

runs.

Never rely on stale values.

---

## AC-6: Do Not Expose Internal Production Fields in UI

The following fields are intended for backend processing only and **must not** be displayed in the UI:

- Production Previous Branch
- Production Commit Anchor
- Production Deployment Timestamp
- Production Environment Details
- Kubernetes Deployment Metadata
- Internal Resolution Metadata

These values should continue to be stored in the database.

---

## AC-7: Display Only Resolution Source

The UI should display only the **Resolution Source**.

Examples:

🟢 PROD_KUBERNETES

🟡 GITHUB_FALLBACK

🔵 USER_OVERRIDE

⚪ MANUAL

No additional production metadata should appear in the grid.

---

## AC-8: Recalculate Resolution Source After User Changes

When the user modifies the Previous Branch manually and proceeds with **Generate Report**:

1. Refresh the latest Production Kubernetes information.
2. Compare the selected Previous Branch with the Production Previous Branch.
3. Recalculate the Resolution Source.

Rules:

If both branches match:

```
Resolution Source = PROD_KUBERNETES
```

If they differ because the user selected another branch:

```
Resolution Source = USER_OVERRIDE
```

If Production lookup failed and GitHub fallback was used:

```
Resolution Source = GITHUB_FALLBACK
```

This calculation must always reflect the latest state and should not rely on previously stored values.

---

## AC-9: Keep Production Metadata in Sync

Every Generate Report execution must refresh:

- Production Previous Branch
- Production Commit SHA
- Branch Cut Status
- Resolution Source

before persisting updates.

---

## AC-10: Helm Repository Must Always Follow Main Repository

This is a mandatory consistency rule.

Example:

Main Repository

```
order-enrichment-ms
```

Helm Repository

```
order-enrichment-ms-helm
```

If the Main Repository resolves:

```
Previous Branch

release/2026.07.18
```

then the Helm Repository must automatically use:

```
release/2026.07.18
```

The Helm repository should never attempt an independent Production Kubernetes lookup.

It must inherit the values from its corresponding Main Repository.

---

## AC-11: Helm Resolution Source

When the Helm branch is inherited from the Main Repository:

```
Resolution Source = PROD_KUBERNETES
```

Do not mark Helm repositories as Manual or GitHub unless the Main Repository itself used those mechanisms.

This ensures complete consistency between Main and Helm repositories.

---

## AC-12: Library Repository Handling

Some repositories are libraries and are **not deployed** into Kubernetes.

Examples include (not limited to):

- Camunda Common Resources
- Camunda Pipeline Resources
- OC-TMF Order Transform
- Other shared libraries configured in Team Configuration

These repositories should not use Production Kubernetes for Previous Branch resolution.

Instead:

- Continue using the existing GitHub-based branch resolution logic.
- Do not attempt Kubernetes lookup.
- Do not mark them as Production resolved.

---

## AC-13: Team Configuration for Libraries

Maintain the list of library repositories in Team Configuration.

For now:

- Continue loading from the Team Configuration (YAML/config).
- Do not hardcode library names.
- Future migration to database configuration is already planned.

---

## AC-14: Library Resolution Source

For library repositories:

```
Resolution Source = GITHUB_FALLBACK
```

unless the user manually changes the branch, in which case:

```
Resolution Source = USER_OVERRIDE
```

---

## AC-15: Preserve Existing Functionality

These enhancements must not impact:

- Fetch Stories
- Fetch Components
- Generate Report
- Review Commits
- Release Readiness
- Deployment Readiness
- Configuration Comparison
- SAST Scan
- Approval Workflow
- Override Workflow
- Existing Branch Comparison Logic

All existing features must continue to work without regression.

---

# Final Expected Behaviour

After Fetch Components:

- Current Branch is resolved using the existing Fix Version logic.
- Branch Cut Status is automatically calculated and stored.
- Production metadata is stored internally but hidden from the UI.
- Only Resolution Source is displayed to users.
- Generate Report recalculates Resolution Source using the latest Production Kubernetes data.
- Helm repositories always inherit branch information from their corresponding Main Repository.
- Library repositories continue using GitHub-based branch resolution.
- All enhancements remain backward compatible and do not break existing functionality.
